t of the written characters must be related to high-sounding things, like he=
aven, moon, gods, light
, splendor, glory, honor, beauty. Later on when the need of the expansion o
f the semantic system arises, lots of them are borrowed to refer to other vu=
lgar things. This suits to the transition of the meaning of =FF=FF=FFfrom th=
e definition I to the definiti
on II. =FF=FF=FF may be used to represent an image of the morning sun, dazzl=
ing an
d radiating, but people finally find it relevant to a boiled food, which is =
